&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic Sister/charge Nurse to join our team. The UIS is a busy Out Patient diagnostic and treatment centre for Urology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work in a newly refurbished suite of 10 clinic rooms offering a wide range of diagnostic tests and treatments. Patients attend as Out Patients but we do also support urgent In Patient cases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The work is exciting and varied. We have a large team, clinical and clerical, and work alongside a large team of Clinical Nurse Specialists and Consultants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will comprise of clinical activity and managerial duties supporting the whole team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Urology experience is essential, training to clinical activity will be provided. The successful candidate will need to possess excellent communication and IT skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Susan Crosby-Jones Matron susan.crosby-jones@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 0300 1314525 ext 770648&lt;/p&gt;
